">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">pursuit of solutions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have taken concrete steps to build o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the past success of the neighbourhood policing model</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but in a manner appropriate to the changed resources landscape</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, and put a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the heart of my tenure the d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sire to reconnect the public with their police by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">coin</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the phrase “Confident </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Commun</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ities”.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">This </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">agenda </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">in many ways </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">seeks to be a 21</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> century iteration of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Peelian</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> principle that the police are the public and the public are the police.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-fa