return to a police station.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am delivering on productivity and visibility and know from regular engagement that I have public support.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In recognition of the fact that the public are the greatest crime fighting tool the police have, I am </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">doubling the number of volunteer police officers and supporting </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Watch schemes and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> other </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">likeminded </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">groups to grow</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In conjunction with the Force and other partners, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I regularly host and attend events to encourage volunteering.  These have included job fairs, freshers’ fairs and Neighbourhood Watch launch events.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">As a result of this extra work and as recently mentioned by Policing Minister Damian Green, applications to volunteer with Bedfordshire Police from BME communities have increased</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> by a third since I took office.  I hope this is the first sign in increasing public confidence. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I maintain there </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">is much more to do </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to raise public confidence and am therefore working with the Chief Constable and her performance department to take steps to improve the management of victims by the police and encourage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a greater proportion of survivors of domestic abuse, sexual abuse and hate crime </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">have the confidence to report.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Working with o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">thers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> - Demand Reduction </span></p><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">On arriving at HQ I was greeted with a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> positive ‘can do’ attitude that I have come </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">to know is typical of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Bedfordshire Police. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Indeed, the Force had already identified that, notwithstanding the circumstances of the election, compared to an unelected Police Authority</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> a PCC could be a useful ally in the field of partnership working and escalating issues into the political realm.  Amongst my 500 plus meetings in my first year, I have met regularly with partners such as other PCCs, Local Council Leaders (including a directly elected Mayor), Directors of Public Health, leaders of Victims’ Services, Probation staff, Judges and many more.</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:12pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am currently undertaking key pieces of work wit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">other forces and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> PCCs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> partner agencies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and increasingly with the non-statutory community to, particularly, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">red</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">uce future demand on services or</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> improve the experience of victims.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">With key partners across the county I am starting to facilitate and shape key pieces of work designed to improve services</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, some of which include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The provision of drug and alcohol treatment services, particularly for those people who need help to deter them from reoffending.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Mental health training for frontline officers and joint protocols for managing those experiencing mental health issues.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Working with the three Community Safety Partnerships</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> in my area</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to develop a countywide action plan for improving the response to hate crime.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span styl